## Summary of Mobile Menu Styling Files

I've found all the CSS and PHP files related to mobile menu styling in your WordPress site. Here are the key locations:

### **PRIMARY FILES - Mobile Menu Background Color**

**1. /Users/dcambria/scripts/server-tools/v2/docker-dev/sites/concertacao/wordpress/wp-content/themes/hello-elementor-child/style.css**

Lines 231-235 define the main mobile menu variables:
```css
--menu-mobile-background         : var(--main-color, #900042);
--menu-mobile-cultura-background : var(--header-submenu-txt, #262834);
--menu-mobile-cultura-text       : var(--main-color, #900042);
--menu-mobile-background-hover   : color-mix(in lab, var(--header-background-submenu, #900042) 80%, black 20%);
--menu-mobile-background-text    : var(--white, #FFFFFF);
```

Also referenced at lines 96-97:
```css
--header-menu-mobile-bg           : var(--e-global-color-784a92e); /* header menu-mobile bg           #000000 */
--header-menu-mobile-txt          : var(--e-global-color-8d6d024); /* header menu-mobile txt          #000000 */
```

**2. /Users/dcambria/scripts/server-tools/v2/docker-dev/sites/concertacao/wordpress/wp-content/themes/hello-elementor-child/css/header-menu.css**

Lines 159-175 contain the actual mobile menu styling:
```css
#menuPrincipal nav.elementor-nav-menu--dropdown {
    background-color: var(--menu-mobile-background) !important;
}

#menuPrincipal nav.elementor-nav-menu--dropdown > ul#menu-2-27229d66.elementor-nav-menu > li.menu-item > a + ul.sub-menu {
    background-color: var(--submenu-background) !important;
    margin          : 0.5rem !important;
    border-radius   : 0.5rem;
}

.elementor-nav-menu .elementor-nav-menu--dropdown ul li a:hover,
.elementor-nav-menu--dropdown ul li a:focus {
    background: var(--menu-mobile-background-hover) !important;
    color     : var(--menu-mobile-background-text, #009) !important;
    outline   : none !important;
    border    : 0 !important;
}
```

### **SECONDARY FILES - Menu Styling**

**3. /Users/dcambria/scripts/server-tools/v2/docker-dev/sites/concertacao/wordpress/wp-content/mu-plugins/bit-inline-submenu.css**

Lines 42-52 define submenu colors (desktop hover bar):
```css
.menu-submenu-inline {
  --bis-bg:                 var(--e-global-color-96a86ed);  /* Color Extra 1 */
  --bis-bg-hover:           var(--e-global-color-96a86ed);  /* Color Extra 1 */
  --bis-text:               var(--e-global-color-4a4a8de);  /* Header Submenu txt */
  --bis-text-hover:         var(--e-global-color-accent);   /* Accent color */
  --bis-text-hover-weight:  700;
  --bis-text-active:        var(--e-global-color-accent);   /* Accent color */
  --bis-border-active:      var(--e-global-color-accent);   /* Accent color */
  --bis-diamond:            var(--bis-bg);
}
```

Hidden on mobile at lines 241-247:
```css
@media (max-width: 1024px) {
  .bit-hover-bar,
  .bit-subnav-bar {
    display: none !important;
  }
}
```

### **PLUGIN FILE - Menu JavaScript**

**4. /Users/dcambria/scripts/server-tools/v2/docker-dev/sites/concertacao/wordpress/wp-content/mu-plugins/bit-inline-submenu.php**

This mu-plugin controls the submenu display on hover and active pages. Key features:
- Line 22-29: Enqueues the CSS file
- Line 33-203: Injects JavaScript that creates hover bars and handles menu interactions
- Inherits CSS variables from the widget (lines 71-76)

**5. /Users/dcambria/scripts/server-tools/v2/docker-dev/sites/concertacao/wordpress/wp-content/mu-plugins/bit-dropdown-btn.php**

Secondary dropdown button styling for file downloads (not primary mobile menu).

### **KEY INFORMATION**

**How Mobile Menu Background Color is Defined:**

1. **Global Color Variable** (style.css): The base variable `--menu-mobile-background` points to `var(--main-color, #900042)` which is the Elementor Global Color "Primary"
2. **Applied in Header Menu** (header-menu.css): Line 160 applies this to `#menuPrincipal nav.elementor-nav-menu--dropdown`
3. **Hover State** (header-menu.css): Line 171 uses `var(--menu-mobile-background-hover)` which is a darkened version created with `color-mix()`
4. **Alternative for /cultura/ Section**: Line 232 in style.css provides `--menu-mobile-cultura-background` with a darker color (#262834)

**Control Point:** To change the mobile menu background color globally, modify the value of `--main-color` or `--menu-mobile-background` in `/Users/dcambria/scripts/server-tools/v2/docker-dev/sites/concertacao/wordpress/wp-content/themes/hello-elementor-child/style.css` at line 231, or update the Elementor Global Colors "Primary" setting in Elementor > Site Settings > Global Colors.

